<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-412-332  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 412 332.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  July 3 1989 n255 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Indiana U. preps for ISDN. (integrated services digital network)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Semilof, Margie.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Indiana University cut over a new $18 million, 18,000-linetelecommunications system that will enable communications betweenits main Bloomington, IN, campus and locations throughout thestate, via the public network.andP;  The Ameritech IntegratedInformation Network (IIN), a central-office-based integrated voiceand data system will be facilitated by a Northern Teleceom DMS-100large business remote switch.andP;  The main campus has been completelyrewired with over one million pairs of copper wire and a fiberoptic backbone, which the university will own along with thetelephone sets.andP;  Integrated Service Digital Network (ISDN)services and Signaling System 7 are both part of an overallstrategic plan to connect faculty and administration, students indormitories and in off-campus housing with ancillary campuslocations around the state.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Indiana Bell Telephone Co. (contracts).andO;Product:   Northern Telecom DSM-100 (Call accounting system) (usage).andO;Topic:     Indiana UniversityTelephone SystemsColleges and UniversitiesIntegrated Voice-DataISDNConnectivityTelecommunications.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>